CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 15, 1961, pg. B5 reads: "Happy Newlyweds - Mr. and Mrs. Rudolph Moses smile happily, following their recent wedding at Bethel AME Church, Pittsburgh. The bride is the former Cloe Virginia Jackson, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. George Jackson of Brownsville. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Rudolph Moses and Cloe Virginia Jackson Moses wearing knee length gown, tiara, and shoulder length veil, standing in front of stained glass window at Bethel AME Church
